en: Den Verstandigen Vroomen ridder, Don Quichot de la Mancha
Willem de Coup, Willem van Lamsveld and Philip Verbeek
Don QUICHOT Ridder van de Leeuwen.

In the foreground, don Quixote, wearing his barber basin, kneels before Dulcinea, who moves away.In the middle ground, Sancho with Rocinante and his donkey (right), Roland and Amadis (center) and Merlin (left).In the background, on a wall-pedestal, don Quixote represented as Knight of the Lions.Good engraving; the frontispiece has been resolved with care; notice some details in faces and gestures.

1 - Frontispiece created with elements after Savery's frontispieces (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).Don Quixote, Sancho, his donkey, Rocinante, Amadis, Roland and Dulcinea appeared in part I frontispiece.Merlin and don Quixote as Knight of the Lion appeared in part II frontispiece.2 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.
In the foreground, Juan Haldudo whipping Andrés, tied to a tree; in the background, don Quixote on Rocinante.Bad drawing and engraving; without details.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote fighting against the Basque / Don Quixote and the windmills
8.2 Adventure of the windmills (giants)8.3 Episode with friars of St. Benedict8.4 Adventure with the Basque

Three different scenes in the same plate (archaic):In the background, the first one: don Quixote attacks the windmills while Sancho tries to stop him.In the middle ground, the second one: Sancho is beaten by the Benedictine monks' servants.In the foreground, don Quixote fights with the Basque, while a Basque lady observes them from her carriage.The Basque holding a stool is not accurate to Cervantes' text; it should be a cushion.Drawing and engraving are acceptable.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
14.1 Episode of Grisóstomo and Marcela, continuation14.2 Grisóstomo´s song14.3 Marcela’s appearance and speech14.4 Burial of Grisóstomo

The background is divided in two parts: underneath, the dead shepherd, his friend Ambrosio, Vivaldo reading Grisóstomo's song and don Quixote; above, Marcela's appearance and speech.Marcela's figure copies saint Gabriel's traditional image.In the foreground, several shepherds digging Grisóstomo's grave.Bad drawing and engraving; faces without details.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).

In the foreground, don Quixote lying on the broken bed; meanwhile, in the background, the fight between Sancho, Maritornes and the muleteer is discovered by the innkeeper, who holds a candle.Bad drawing and engraving.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
25.1 DQ as Beltenebros proposes to do penance for Dulcinea25.4 SP’s embassy to Dulcinea;25.5 DQ performs mad acts
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Sancho's blanketing / Don Quixote fighting with a flock of sheep

Two different scenes in the same plate (archaic):In the foreground, Sancho's blanketing is observed by don Quixote from behind the inn wall.In the background, don Quixote fighting with a flock of sheep.Simple composition that will be used until the 20th century.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote and Sancho release the galley slaves
22.1 Adventure of the galley slaves (galeotes)22.4 Liberation of galeotes
In the foreground, Sancho releases the galley slaves while, in the background, don Quixote fights with one of the slave guards.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Mad Cardenio attacks don Quixote and Sancho
In Sierra Morena, Mad Cardenio attacks don Quixote and Sancho; the goather tries to help them.Acceptable drawing and engraving, but poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Doin Quixote begins his love penance
25.4 SP’s embassy to Dulcinea;25.5 DQ performs mad acts

Sancho, with a huge broom bunch (accurate to Cervantes' text), leaves for El Toboso mounted on Rocinante, while don Quixote remains doing penance (half-naked, doing a somersault in an undecorous manner).Don Quixote's arms hung on a tree.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).

Dorotea (Micomicona) prevents don Quixote from punishing Sancho for having preferred her beauty to Dulcinea's.Also the priest, Cardenio and the barber, disguised as Micomicona's page with a fake beard.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
36.2 Resolution of love affairs of Cardenio and Luscinda, Dorotea and Don Fernando

Dorotea recognises don Fernando and Luscinda, who has lost her mask (tafetán), and, knelt before don Fernando, begs him to let Luscinda go with Cardenio; Sancho, the priest and the barber observe them.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote hung and tied to the inn window
43.2 Maritornes and innkeeper’s daughter hang DQ from window by a hand43.3 Four travelers arrive at inn

Don Quixote falls from Rocinante and remains hung and tied by his hand to a window when four travelers (servants of don Luis' father) arrive to the inn. Rocinante has moved to smell one of the mares.The innkeeper appears to discover who is shouting.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Bad copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote meets the enchanted Dulcinea
10.2 The three labradoras10.3 SP presents to DQ the enchanted Dulcinea

Don Quixote and Sancho kneel before one peasant girl introduced by Sancho as the enchanted Dulcinea; also two more peasant girls on donkeys.Good drawing and engraving; notice some details in expressions and faces.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Sancho's donkey stolen by the bojiganga
11.1 Adventure of the cart of actors; “cortes de la muerte”

The bojiganga steals Sancho's donkey while the squire goes to don Quixote's assistance (falling with Rocinante in the background).In the cart, the actors of Angulo el Malo's company for theCortes de la Muerte(Devil, Cupid, Death, Angel, Emperor, Queen and Soldier); there is one additional player not from Cervantes' text.Drawing and engraving are acceptable.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).

In the foreground, don Quixote is ready to fight with a lion while the lionkeeper opens the gate of the cage.In the background, Sancho and don Diego de Miranda running away.This composition, with not many changes, will be used until the 20th century.Drawing and engraving are bad.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote at the entry of Montesinos' cave
22.2 Adventure of the cave of Montesinos

Don Quixote is surprised by a flock of birds when he tries to descend into Montesinos' cave.Sancho Panza and the bachelor's cousin hold the rope to which don Quixote is tied.Drawing and engraving are poor, although some details have been represented with care.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote attacking Maese Pedro's theater
26.1 Episode of Maese Pedro26.3 DQ attacks and destroys the puppets

Don Quixote standing to attack Maese Pedro's theater while several astonished witnesses observe him.Maese Pedro appears from under the theater.Theatrical gestures, but without force.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Don Quixote and Sancho attacked by the members of the braying mayors squadron

Sancho, beaten by one of the members of the braying mayors squadron, falls from his donkey and don Quixote gets ready to attack them.Lances are multiplied to suggest agitation and a more numerous group.Drawing and engraving are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
Sancho chased by Duke's servants to wash his beard

In the foreground, Sancho bursts into the room followed by Duke's servants, who want to wash his beard with dirty water and towels.In the background, the Duke, the Duchess and don Quixote.Drawing, engraving and setting are poor.
1 - Same plate first used for Amsterdam: Willem van Lamsveld, 1696.2 – Copy after Savery’s plate (Dordrecht: Savery, 1657).
